<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="164" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,773,1201,2023]" pageId="31" pageNumber="164">
The taxon was described from a male from Ofotford (
<collectingCountry box="[158,247,1297,1318]" name="Norway" pageId="31" pageNumber="164">Norway</collectingCountry>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[259,359,1297,1319]" degrees="68.43" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="31" pageNumber="164" precision="555" value="68.43">68.43° N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[371,465,1297,1318]" degrees="17.03" direction="east" orientation="longitude" pageId="31" pageNumber="164" precision="555" value="17.03">17.03° E</geoCoordinate>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="ZETTERSTEDT" box="[485,713,1297,1319]" firstAuthor="ZETTERSTEDT" pageId="31" pageNumber="164" pagination="317 - 475" refId="ref47777" refString="ZETTERSTEDT, J. W. 1838: Insecta Lapponica. Sectio secunda. Hymenoptera. - L. Voss, Lipsiae [= Leipzig], pp. 317 - 475." type="book chapter" year="1838">ZETTERSTEDT (1838)</bibRefCitation>
’s description matches all three species expected to occur at the Ofotford: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="ZETTERSTEDT" authorityYear="1838" box="[268,390,1361,1382]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Formica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="164" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lugubris">
<emphasis box="[268,390,1361,1382]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="164">F. lugubris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[404,619,1361,1382]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="164">
<taxonomicName box="[404,616,1361,1382]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Formica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="164" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aquilonia">Formica aquilonia</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Formica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="164" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="truncorum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="164">Formica truncorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="YARROW" box="[288,460,1392,1414]" firstAuthor="YARROW" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Society for British Entomology" pageId="31" pageNumber="164" pagination="1 - 48" part="12" refId="ref47744" refString="YARROW, I. H. H. 1955: The British ants allied to Formica rufa L. - Transactions of the Society for British Entomology 12: 1 - 48." title="The British ants allied to Formica rufa L" type="journal article" year="1955">YARROW (1955)</bibRefCitation>
, who was the first after 120 years to revive 
<taxonomicName authorityName="ZETTERSTEDT" authorityYear="1838" box="[319,440,1425,1446]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Formica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="164" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lugubris">
<emphasis box="[319,440,1425,1446]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="164">F. lugubris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from synonymy and to give it a status of a good species, did not explain on which basis he identified J.W. Zetterstedt’s male. All later authors (including me) followed 
<bibRefCitation author="YARROW" box="[412,579,1520,1542]" firstAuthor="YARROW" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Society for British Entomology" pageId="31" pageNumber="164" pagination="1 - 48" part="12" refId="ref47744" refString="YARROW, I. H. H. 1955: The British ants allied to Formica rufa L. - Transactions of the Society for British Entomology 12: 1 - 48." title="The British ants allied to Formica rufa L" type="journal article" year="1955">YARROW (1955)</bibRefCitation>
’s diagnosis based on workers and gynes and kept silent regarding the male problem. J.W. Zetterstedt’s 
<typeStatus box="[470,520,1585,1606]" pageId="31" pageNumber="164">type</typeStatus>
male is, according to 
<bibRefCitation author="YARROW" box="[151,328,1616,1638]" firstAuthor="YARROW" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Society for British Entomology" pageId="31" pageNumber="164" pagination="1 - 48" part="12" refId="ref47744" refString="YARROW, I. H. H. 1955: The British ants allied to Formica rufa L. - Transactions of the Society for British Entomology 12: 1 - 48." title="The British ants allied to Formica rufa L" type="journal article" year="1955">YARROW (1955)</bibRefCitation>
, stored in 
<collectionCode box="[452,524,1617,1638]" country="Sweden" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/nzgn-b6sw" name="Lunds Universitet, Zoologiska Institutionen" pageId="31" pageNumber="164">ZMLU</collectionCode>
Lund. If still present there, its identity can only be determined after a thorough, broad-based study on male characters at least in the Fennoscandian population of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="ZETTERSTEDT" authorityYear="1838" box="[435,555,1713,1734]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Formica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="164" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lugubris">
<emphasis box="[435,555,1713,1734]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="164">F. lugubris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[567,699,1713,1734]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Formica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="164" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aquilonia">
<emphasis box="[567,699,1713,1734]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="164">F. aquilonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Formica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="164" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="truncorum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="164">F. truncorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
– at least it remains to be investigated if the differential characters proposed in the keys of 
<bibRefCitation author="KUTTER" firstAuthor="KUTTER" journalOrPublisher="Fauna Insecta Helvetica" pageId="31" pageNumber="164" pagination="1 - 298" part="6" refId="ref46033" refString="KUTTER, H. 1977: Hymenoptera Formicidae. - Fauna Insecta Helvetica 6: 1 - 298." title="Hymenoptera Formicidae" type="journal article" year="1977">KUTTER (1977)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="CZECHOWSKI" bookContentInfo="496 pp." box="[274,541,1809,1831]" etAl="&amp; al." firstAuthor="CZECHOWSKI" journalOrPublisher="Natura optima dux Foundation, Warszawa" pageId="31" pageNumber="164" refId="ref45078" refString="CZECHOWSKI, W., FOREL, A., CZECHOWSKA, W. &amp; VEPSALAINEN, K. 2012: The ants of Poland with reference to the myrmecofauna of Europe. - Natura optima dux Foundation, Warszawa, 496 pp." title="The ants of Poland with reference to the myrmecofauna of Europe" type="book" year="2012">CZECHOWSKI &amp; al. (2012)</bibRefCitation>
for the Central European population do apply to the boreal populations of these species.
</paragraph>
